summary: I love how relatively drama-free the Good Omens fandom is tbh like really the only thing I dislike about it is that I cringe...
body:
I love how relatively drama-free the Good Omens fandom is tbh like really the only thing I dislike about it is that I cringe every time Crowley says “Zira” instead of “Aziraphale” because I do not like associating my beloved prissy angel bookstore owner with the evil lioness from Lion King 2

But even then like… sure. Some people like drawing Crowley and Aziraphale young when I prefer them older. Some people like drawing Aziraphale skinnier when I prefer him fatter. Some people call Aziraphale Zira and I cringe away from any attempt to shorten his name. And that’s… fine. 

To each their own, because at least we can all agree pretty much unanimously in this fandom that these two idiots love each other.
